questions.question_text:
A 22-year-old medical student presents with fatigue and muscle weakness after prolonged exercise. Laboratory tests show elevated levels of muscle glycogen and no rise in blood lactate after exercise.
Which enzyme is most likely deficient in this patient?
questions.hint: Think about an enzyme that breaks down glycogen in skeletal muscle to release glucose during anaerobic exercise. If this enzyme is missing → muscle cannot get energy → cramps + no lactate increase.

options.option_text:
A. Glucose-6-phosphatase
B. Debranching enzyme
C. Muscle phosphorylase
D. Acid maltase (α-1,4-glucosidase)
E. Branching enzyme
options.explanation: Debranching enzyme

questions.question_text:
A 22-year-old medical student presents with fatigue and muscle weakness after prolonged exercise. Laboratory tests show elevated levels of muscle glycogen and no rise in blood lactate after exercise.
Which enzyme is most likely deficient in this patient?
questions.hint: Think about an enzyme that breaks down glycogen in skeletal muscle to release glucose during anaerobic exercise. If this enzyme is missing → muscle cannot get energy → cramps + no lactate increase.

options.option_text:
A. Glucose-6-phosphatase
B. Debranching enzyme
C. Muscle phosphorylase
D. Acid maltase (α-1,4-glucosidase)
E. Branching enzyme
options.explanation: Debranching enzyme
